Probabilistic Methods, Case Based

Explanation: 

Probabilistic Methods: The Diverse Density framework described in the paper is based on probabilistic methods. It uses a probabilistic model to estimate the probability of a bag being positive or negative based on the instances it contains.

Case Based: The paper describes the application of the Diverse Density framework to learn a simple description of a person from a series of images (bags) containing that person. This is an example of a case-based approach, where the system learns from specific instances (bags) rather than general rules.
